title: IOS build error replacing existing signature unknown error -1=ffffffffffffffff
body:
When buidling Xamarin.Forms project (from visual studio on a PC), the IOS build will fail with the following error: 

/Users/ericbourque/Library/Caches/Xamarin/mtbs/builds/SentinelMobile.iOS/ec3fa8c87274cfb85c8423bb8f475608/bin/iPhone/Debug/SentinelMobile.iOS.app/Frameworks/libSkiaSharp.framework/libSkiaSharp: replacing existing signature
/Users/ericbourque/Library/Caches/Xamarin/mtbs/builds/SentinelMobile.iOS/ec3fa8c87274cfb85c8423bb8f475608/bin/iPhone/Debug/SentinelMobile.iOS.app/Frameworks/libSkiaSharp.framework/libSkiaSharp: unknown error -1=ffffffffffffffff	SentinelMobile.iOS

comments.author: mattleibow
comments.body:
There may be a problem with your Xcode installation, or your iOS setup.
If you create a new iOS app, without SkiaSharp, does it run on your device? Then, if that works, Can you add SkiaSharp to that app and does it fail? If it does, could you send/attach your build log?

For testing purposes, I usually use this set of samples:
https://github.com/mattleibow/SkiaSharpDemo

You can also try those and see if it builds.

comments.author: tougher
comments.body:
I have the same issue, but only when building/signing from the command line with _msbuild_. It has building/signing perfectly with the deprecated _xbuild_, but now I need _netstandard 2.0_ support which breaks to build in _xbuild_ (https://github.com/dotnet/core/issues/862).

I don't think it's a SkiaSharp issue and I have no idea of how to fix it, but I'm puzzled about why _xbuild_ can sign the build but _msbuild_ can not.

This SO post has an answer that makes no sense to me (and my build setup): https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45440727/codesign-returns-unknown-error-after-replacing-existing-signature

comments.author: ebourque29
comments.body: I do not think it's a SkiaSharp error either but if it happened to me other uses could face the same issue. I will try to make more tests this week. I will delete all signatures/provisioning profiles I created and make new ones.

comments.author: ebourque29
comments.body:
Sorry for the delay. Issue was having multiple certificates and provisioning profiles.

The automatic signing did not know which profile to use.

Solution steps that worked for me:

1. Delete and revoke all certificates, app id's and provisioning profiles in Apple Developper
2. Delete all keychains in MAC used for compiling that contain your certificate or app id
3. Make new ones with different names that you can easilly identify (the old ones will still be in the Visual Studio list)

4. Enjoy a clean compilation.

If anyone knows a better way to do this please post here:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46111418/xamarin-forms-ios-error-replacing-existing-signature

comments.author: mattleibow
comments.body: I was also having some issues like this and did exactly that. It appeared after upgrading xcode. Did you upgrade at all?

comments.author: ericbourque29
comments.body: Yes, everything is up to the latest version.

comments.author: tougher
comments.body: There has to be a regression in _msbuild_. I can build and sign apps perfectly with _xbuild_ / _xcodebuild_, but _msbuild_ requires a special setup of certificates and profiles. One would expect it just to work with whatever Xcode is doing automatically. I would like to file a bug at the Xamarin bugzilla, but I don't know where to start :-/

comments.author: mattleibow
comments.body:
For MSBuild / XBuild, you can start here:
https://bugzilla.xamarin.com/enter_bug.cgi?product=Tools

Just select the "msbuild" item from the "Component:" list box.

comments.author: tougher
comments.body: @mattleibow Thanks, but I was to vague in my last comment :-) I have submitted bug to the bugzilla before, but I don't know how to put a good bug description together for at complex bug like this. Maybe I'll do it soon, when I need to setup new builds agents or maybe I'll give fastlane/cert a try.

comments.author: nathanielcook
comments.body:
For others that run into this cryptic error, this is what fixed it for me on two separate occasions on a build server: 

1. Build your app from the terminal (on macOS) with msbuild.
2. If it pops up asking you something like _"codesign wants to access key 'foo' in your keychain. To allow this, enter the 'login' keychain password"_, then enter the password and be sure to tap "always allow".

After that it remembered and I was able to build without the `ffffffffffffffff` error.
